What is Counting Coup?

Counting coup was a relatively harmless act of bravery and war honor of the highest grade. Any blow struck against the enemy counted as a coup, but the most prestigious acts included touching an enemy warrior, with the hand or with a coup stick.The term is of French origin from the noun coup (pronounced /ku/) which means a hit, a blow or a strike. The expression can be seen as referring to "counting strikes". Coups were recorded by notches in the coup stick, or by feathers in the headdress of a warrior who was rewarded with them for an act of bravery.

Origins-
Tribesk8z started as a creative outlet for art therapy during D.J.’s transition from the military.
It combined his childhood passion for skateboarding and the power of art therapy to get him through some of his darkest moments. 
It was calming, forced him to focus his attention on something new and outside of his normal routine.
The team slowly started to grow and eventually became a safe haven for transitioning service members and Gold Star families through employment.
Through our growth we have been able to sponsor a few young hungry skaters and help them progress through support. 
Zander is a local shredder that we started sponsoring shortly after we opened the company. His passion for skating is palpable and his energy is unmatched - we couldn’t be more proud to see how far he has come and are excited to watch him grow in this sport. 
Most people don’t know but GBRS Group was founded in a 500 Sft office that Tribesk8z was occupying back in 2019.
The plan was to grow as needed, employ those closest to us, build a community and culture that was a family more than a work force. 
In the last 3 years we have grown to 30 employees and helped so many people find purpose and stability through employment and community. 
That little side project Tribesk8z that was only really designed to help DJ, set in motion something we never could have planned for. 
We are beyond grateful for the opportunities we have been given and have no plans of slowing down.
From the entire family here at Tribesk8z and GBRS Group, thank you for all the support, we look forward to watching the companies grow and the community build even stronger.

Extremely grateful-
It’s the only way to sum up the support we’ve had at Tribesk8z since day one and it’s definitely taken on a few different roles over the years. It was started as a form of art therapy and mental health awareness and quickly transitioned into a lifestyle brand that connected many cultures together as a Tribe. It’s been a mechanism to raise funding for gold star and injured service members and first responders. It was also the birthplace of GBRS group and helped shape the culture that is the lifeblood of the company. 
Tribesk8z also had the unique ability to sponsor several up and coming skaters and helped them progress over the last 5 days. We are so grateful for you and your support to this brand, watching you ride our decks was a highlight in all of our lives and catch waiters to see your next chapter unfold. 
Our first employees were strictly volunteers who were just helping us because that’s the type of people they are, we truly appreciate every one of you and the individual time you gifted us as we build the company. 
Over the last 5 years the employees have shaped every inch of the building and the brand.
Individual long hours and a process that required you to find your flow state, the fractal burned boards are a separate skill altogether and a process that not everyone gets to be a part of.…(continued pinned comment)
